<item>
            <title>[LU-1501] Kernel panic - not syncing: Cannot find space for the kernel page tables</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1501</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of our, DDN Japan, customer faced kernel panic with RIP in &quot;RIP  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa07a32e3&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ll_readahead+0x43/0x1d20 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;lustre&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Attached is the console log of this client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you check if this is Kernel/BIOS issue or Lustre issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Many thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Minoru@DDN Japan&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Clients: SGI UV1000&lt;br/&gt;
kernel: 2.6.32-131.0.15.el6.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
lustre: 1.8.7 wc1</environment>
